    Serializable, DomainObject

    public class FinalConsistencyPredicate
extends FinalConsistencyPredicate_Base
    A FinalConsistencyPredicate is a PublicConsistencyPredicate that represents a predicate method that is either public or protected, and is final. It can override other PublicConsistencyPredicates, but cannot be overridden. Therefore, during the initialization, unlike the PublicConsistencyPredicate, the execution of a new FinalConsistencyPredicate does not need to check subclasses for overriding methods.
